<div class="hgroup"><h1 class="title"><span class="title">03. Solving mode</span></h1></div>
<div class="region">
<div class="contents">
<div class="media media-image"><div class="inner"><img src="figures/solving-mode.png" height="400" width="350" alt=""></div></div>
<p class="p"> When Gnonograms is in "solving" mode, it displays the "working grid". This grid starts with all grey (unknown) cells.
	</p>
<p class="p"> When in "solving" mode, you can:
	</p>
<div class="list"><div class="inner"><div class="region"><ul class="list">
<li class="list"><p class="p"> Solve the puzzle manually by drawing on the grid
		</p></li>
<li class="list"><p class="p"> Check your progress for errors
		</p></li>
<li class="list"><p class="p"> Let the computer solve the puzzle (if it can!)
		</p></li>
<li class="list"><p class="p"> Save a partially finished puzzle
		</p></li>
<li class="list"><p class="p"> Reveal the solution by switching back to design mode
		</p></li>
</ul></div></div></div>
</div>
